# Active surfaces

Most behavior changes in `tc-experiment` land in one of these files.
When a task is unclear, start by checking whether the change belongs in
one of them before searching elsewhere.

## Hot files

- [src/lib/workflow/intake.ts](mdc:src/lib/workflow/intake.ts) — main inbound-email orchestrator (~800 lines; ~60% activity logging). Sequences match -> assess -> decide -> policy -> execute. Step-by-step: [docs/pipelines/intake.md](mdc:docs/pipelines/intake.md).
- [src/lib/db/repositories.ts](mdc:src/lib/db/repositories.ts) — every SQL statement the app runs (~1336 lines). Aggregate-to-line-range map: [src/lib/db/README.md](mdc:src/lib/db/README.md).
- [src/lib/agent/decision.ts](mdc:src/lib/agent/decision.ts) — LLM call that picks `AgentIntent` + `AgentAction` from a closed enum. System prompt lives here. Fallback decision lives here too.
- [src/lib/agent/executor.ts](mdc:src/lib/agent/executor.ts) — acts on the decision: sends emails, creates approval requests, records `agent_decisions` outcomes, emits audit events.
- [src/lib/agent/activity.ts](mdc:src/lib/agent/activity.ts) — activity event types, source / status enums, body-preview + status-mapping helpers. Observability only.
- [src/lib/agent/activity-timeline.ts](mdc:src/lib/agent/activity-timeline.ts) — adapters that turn legacy records (messages, documents, decisions, approvals, audit) into synthetic activity events for older transactions. Pure mapping.
- [src/lib/documents/attachments.ts](mdc:src/lib/documents/attachments.ts) — fetch attachments from AgentMail, store in Vercel Blob, write `documents` rows, log document-related activity.

